    • allocateAnElevatorHelper

      private int[] allocateAnElevatorHelper​(CallForElevator c)
      the "Brain" of the algorithm. hold 2 steps to prioritize via the helper main functions: 1- elevators in the same "type" of mission OR elevators in LEVEL state 2- all the elevators if we find at ea step even 1 elevator relevant, func return ID of an elevator from that category
      Parameters:
      c - - CallForElevator the correct call which we're trying to work on
      Returns:
      optimal elevator ID for this task.

    • sumOfFloors

      private int sumOfFloors​(Elevator elevator, int src, int dest, int stopCountTillSrc, int stopCountTillDest)
      summarize absolute number of floors that the elevator going to go through example: if the elevator position is 1 and the dest floor is 10, but there is few missions before this tasks which is: going to floor 7 than to floor 3 the sumOf floors returns: 1->7->3->10 => 6+4+7 = 17
      Parameters:
      elevator - - relevant elevator
      dest -
      stopCountTillSrc - - idx - where we shall add the srcFloor of the task => means that's the position which we shall count till.
      stopCountTillDest - - same as above, just with the destFloor
      Returns:

    • addOnlyIfNoDuplicates

      private boolean addOnlyIfNoDuplicates​(int idx, int floorNum, java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.Integer> eList)
      add a num to linkedList ONLY if not a duplicate. duplicate means => after added if the value at idx-1 OR the value at idx+1 is SAME (ONLY one of them is enough)
      Parameters:
      idx - where to add
      floorNum - - value to add
      eList - - LinkedList
      Returns:
      TRUE if added, FALSE if not added
